  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In order to describe quantitatively the strong or weak decays of heavy particles into two π(K)-mesons one needs to know the behaviour of the π-meson wave function ϕ π ( x ) which determines the quark longitudinal momentum distribution inside the π-meson, p 1 = xp π , p 2 = (1 − x ) p π , p π → ∞). We calculate the few first moments 〈 ξ 2 n 〉 ≡ ∫ −1 1 d ξξ 2 n ϕ π ( ξ ), ξ = 2 x − 1 of the π-meson wave function using the QCD sum rules, and show that sum rules give strong restrictions on the values of the moments 〈 ξ 2 n 〉. Based on these results we discuss the qualitative behaviour of ϕ π ( x ) and propose the model wave function.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
